<HEADLINE>
<P>
HEALTH CARE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Regarding Donella Meadows' suggestions on health care (Commentary, May 13): 
</P>
<P>
 Her words make up the clearest and most logical statement expressed to date. 
She is correct in asserting that it makes no difference whether health-care 
costs are paid to the government and called taxes, or to insurance companies 
and called premiums. 
</P>
<P>
 By reducing "bureaucracy, advertising, lobbying, litigating, stockholders, 
lush corporate offices and exorbitant executive salaries," health care no 
longer is a profit-making enterprise dominated by insurance companies. 
</P>
<P>
 Nor do I have more faith in the medical decisions of insurance companies 
rather than those of a broad citizens' committee made up of non-professional 
and professional citizens. Their aim only need be giving the best and the most 
to the most people. 
</P>
<P>
 A simple workable single-payer system can evolve ultimately. Let us begin to 
work it out now and thank you, Donella Meadows. 
</P>
<P>
 GORDON STONE MD 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
