</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fullerton's Jenny Lee beat Kellee Booth of Coto de Caza on the second playoff 
hole to win the Girls' Junior Championships tournament Monday in Tucson. 
</P>
<P>
 Booth, the defending champion, started the third round on the 6,133-yard, 
par-72 Sunrise course at El Conquistador Country Club two strokes ahead of Lee. 
</P>
<P>
 Lee, who is a junior at Sunny Hills High, shot one-under-par 71, Booth, who is 
a senior at Santa Margarita, shot 73 and they each finished one-under 215 for 
three rounds, six shots ahead of third-place Grace Park of Phoenix. 
</P>
<P>
 Booth, the reigning U.S. Junior Girls' Champion who will attend Arizona State, 
had shot 68 in the first round Saturday, and shot 74 Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Jenny Glasgow, a sophomore at Corona del Mar High, shot 78 to finish with 236, 
in a tie for 22nd place. 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Berry, a senior at Esperanza, finished in a three-way tie for 22nd place 
at the ClubCorp Junior Championship in Akron, Ohio. Berry shot two-over 74 at 
Firestone Country Club to finish with a three-day total of 232. The winner, 
Michael Boyd of Tulsa, Okla., shot 211, 11 strokes ahead of second place. 
</P>
