<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPECIAL WORLD REPORT: A LOOK BACK AT D-DAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fifty years ago, Allied soldiers stormed the Normandy beaches to roll back the 
Nazis. D-day, the battle and its legacies. A World Report special edition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Infobox 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA053194-0056 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 046867 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
May 31, 1994, Tuesday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Part A; Page 1; Column 1; Metro Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
311 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jerry Hick; Davan Maharaj, ; Frank Messina 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 PRE-ASSAULT: Bob Hope's TV special about D-day next Monday night on NBC will 
be special to Richard T. Headrick, 77, of Irvine. When Hope learned that 
Headrick had been an adviser to Dwight D. Eisenhower on bombing strategies at 
Normandy, he asked him to his home in Toluca Lake to be interviewed for the 
show. . . . "Unfortunately, I ended up on the cutting room floor," Headrick 
says with a chuckle. "But my visit with Bob was delightful." 
</P>
<P>
 HISTORIC MEAL? Residents at the Palm Terrace Retirement Home in Laguna Hills 
are recalling life on the home front during the D-day era with a World War II 
recipe book. It's selling throughout South County for $3, and includes 
wholesome meals like Marge Mackessy's pork chop and potato casserole. Says 
Mackessy: "When my three sons came home from the war, I made each of them what 
they wanted -- but they all liked this!" 
</P>
<P>
 HAPPY DAY: The Orange County Bar Assn. wanted a prominent jurist for the July 
15 groundbreaking of the Ronald Reagan U.S. Courthouse at Santa Ana's Civic 
Center. It got one. . . . Sandra Day O'Connor, a Reagan appointee and the first 
woman on the U.S. Supreme Court, will join a celebration at Le Meridien hotel 
in Newport Beach. "It's the first time that a Supreme Court justice has ever 
been here for a bar event," says Arthur Nakazato, a bar official. "And Justice 
O'Connor wanted to attend this event for a very special reason." 
</P>
<P>
 ORANGE SLICKER I: A support group for the county Probation Department has 
finagled a special Orange County premiere for "City Slickers II." It's a 
red-carpet, $100 per ticket fund-raiser Thursday night to help juvenile 
delinquents. . . . There's a buffet at Roxbury South at Santa Ana's Hutton 
Centre, followed by the movie next door at the Edwards Cinema. Will Billy 
Crystal be there? "He's iffy," says a spokesman. "But we did get Bo Derek and 
Lorenzo Lamas." 
</P>
