EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS : THOUSAND OAKS; REWARD OFFERED FOR TIPS ON SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A reward of up to $1,000 is being offered by Ventura County Crime Stoppers for 
information about a drive-by shooting at a Thousand Oaks party earlier this 
month. 
</P>
<P>
 The shooting occurred about 9:40 p.m. on May 20, in the 1200 block of 
Sheffield Street.Party-goers were in front of a house when three young men 
approached and asked where they were from. 
</P>
<P>
 When no one answered, one man yelled out a gang name and started shooting, 
sending the party-goers scurrying for cover. No one was hurt, said Ventura 
County Sheriff's Sgt. Kitty Hoberg. But investigators found bullet holes in a 
truck, and a tire was slashed, Hoberg said. 
</P>
<P>
 "All we have is a description of these guys, and it's a pretty generic 
description," Hoberg said. "I think some of the witnesses are a little 
intimidated." 
</P>
<P>
 Callers to Crime Stoppers may remain anonymous and do not have to fear 
retaliation, Hoberg said. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone with information about the shooting may call Crime Stoppers at 
494-TALK. PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
