<P>
 Courses for Entrepreneurs: The Accelerate Technology Small Business 
Development Center, sponsored by the U.S. Small Business Administration and 
UCI's Graduate School of Management, is offering a series of courses for 
entrepreneurs beginning June 8. 
</P>
<P>
 The first of the four courses, held weekly on Wednesday nights from 6 to 10 
p.m., is titled "Finding Critical Information for New Ventures."Participants 
will look at ways to analyze the potential success of an idea for a business. 
</P>
<P>
 On June 15, students will learn marketing strategies; and in the June 22 
class, how to assemble and understand balance sheets, income statements and 
cash flow. In the final class, June 29, entrepreneurs will learn how to 
assemble a business plan and attract funding. 
</P>
