<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LA HABRA; SENIORS' CARETAKERS CAN ATTEND CLASS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 People who care for older relatives are being invited to attend a free class 
to learn how to reduce stress.The two-day class will be held Thursday and June 
9 at the Friendly Hills Regional Medical Center, 1211 W. Lambert Road. 
</P>
<P>
 It will emphasize organization skills and offer tips on how to work with 
community resources, managing financial and legal issues and making decisions 
regarding the care of the elderly, hospital officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 To enroll, call (310) 905-4595. MIMI KO 
</P>
