<P>
 Drillers Find Oil Off Cuban Coast: Foreign companies and Cubapetroleo, the 
state oil agency, said they have discovered crude oil in Cuba's Bay of 
Cardenas.The well, first drilled Dec. 18, reached a total depth of 10,670 feet 
and tested 16-degree API oil at a rate of 3,750 barrels per day, the companies 
said. The size is under evaluation. Canada Northwest Energy Ltd. has a 60% 
interest in the well. A discovery of significant size would throw a lifeline to 
Cuba, which is facing severe economic crisis since the collapse of its old 
trade and aid partner, the Soviet Union. 
