<TEXT>
<P>
 I spend Downtime reading and talking to Gilbert. When this parakeet came to 
me, I thought we'd have an idyllic future.When the earthquake came, Gilbert 
stopped asking, "How are ya? Where you been?" His feathers were as shaken as my 
courage. I began to read poetry aloud. Everyday I asked, "Feeling better?" 
