<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: CHAD THERAPEUTICS REPORTS RECORD EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chad Therapeutics Inc., a Chatsworth maker of oxygen-conserving devices used 
by patients with respiratory problems, reported record earnings for its fiscal 
fourth quarter on a 56% surge in revenue. 
</P>
<P>
 For the quarter that ended March 31, the company's profit climbed 77%, to 
$564,577 from $318,893 in the comparable period a year earlier. Sales in the 
latest quarter were $2.47 million, up from $1.58 million, partly on the 
strength of its new portable oxygen system introduced in November. 
</P>
<P>
 For its fiscal year that ended March 31, Chad's profit boomed 65%, to $2.05 
million from $1.24 million a year earlier. Its latest fiscal year sales totaled 
$9.47 million, up 63% from $5.8 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
