<P>
VENTURA COUNTY REVIEW: VENTURA FIRM TO DESIGN DEL MONTE WAREHOUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jack Searles 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Essence Engineering Inc., based in Ventura, has been chosen to design and 
oversee construction of a $3.6-million refrigerated warehouse for Del Monte 
Fresh Produce Inc. at the Port of Hueneme. 
</P>
<P>
 The 40,000-square-foot building will be used to store bananas and melons 
imported mostly from Central America, Essence President Richard Kasa reported. 
</P>
<P>
 He said construction will begin in September and should be completed by March. 
</P>
<P>
 Essence also did the engineering work on the nearby $3.5-million BMW plant on 
Hueneme Road in Oxnard, where cars are processed after being brought into the 
country through the port. 
</P>
