<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: DANA POINT; CULTURAL ARTS SHOW, FOOD FAIRE PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Elementary and middle-school students and their families from throughout South 
County are invited to the first Cultural Arts Festival & Showcase and 
International Food Faire on Saturday at Dana Point Harbor. 
</P>
<P>
 The day of family activities includes dancers, theatrical groups, a symphony 
and an orchestra as well as an array of ethnic foods. 
</P>
<P>
 The event, which is sponsored by the Richard Henry Dana Institute for the 
Arts, will run from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. at the Dana Point Youth & Group Facility, 
34451 Ensenada Place. 
</P>
<P>
 The city of Dana Point has designated the institute as the city's arts agency 
to promote multicultural arts and arts education. Institute officials said they 
hope to make the festival an annual event. 
</P>
<P>
 Festival organizers are asking for a donation of $3 for adults and $1.50 for 
children to help offset costs. 
</P>
<P>
 Featured will be performances by Folklorico de Los Ninos, Capistrano Valley 
Symphony, Master Chorale of Orange County Children's Chorus, Sea Strings, South 
Orange County Community Theatre, Pacific Theatre, Pacific Symphony, Opera 
Pacific, Laguna Playhouse, Ballet Folklorico and the South Coast Storytellers 
Guild. 
</P>
<P>
 The International Food Faire is to include food from Norway, Italy, France, 
Thailand, Mexico, Spain, China and Greece. 
</P>
</TEXT>
