<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; R.H. DANA STUDENT WINS ART CONTEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JODI WILGOREN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Megan Nelms, a first-grader at Richard Henry Dana Elementary School, has won 
first place in the California Young Farmer Educational Assn.Coloring Contest. 
</P>
<P>
 Her entry, a drawing of carrots growing underground, earned her a plaque and a 
$100 savings bond. 
</P>
<P>
 It was displayed at the state Department of Food and Agriculture, the state 
Capitol and the Sacramento Metro Airport. 
</P>
<P>
 More than 23,000 entries were submitted to the contest, designed to increase 
agricultural awareness. JODI WILGOREN 
</P>
</TEXT>
