There," edited by Ronald J. Drez 
</P>
<P>
 "Assault on Normandy: First Person Accounts from the Sea Services," edited by 
Paul Stillwell. 
</P>
<P>
 "Parachute Infantry: An American Paratrooper's Memoir of D-Day and the Fall of 
the Third Reich," David Kenyon Webster 
</P>
<P>
 "D-Day With The Screaming Eagles," George E. Koskimaki 
</P>
<P>
 "Overlord: D-Day, June 6, 1944," Max Hastings 
</P>
<P>
 "D-Day," Warren Tute 
</P>
<P>
 Sources: Atlanta Journal; "D-Day, June 6, 1944: The Climactic Battle of World 
War II," by Stephen E. Ambrose; Associated Press; "D-Day," by Warren Tute; "The 
D-Day Encyclopedia"; American History magazine; U.S. Army Center of Military 
History; "Decision in Normandy"; Encyclopaedia Britannica. 
